{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}} The '''Justice Erima Harvey Northcroft Tokyo War Crimes Trial Collection''' is an archival collection held at the [[Macmillan Brown Library]] of [[Canterbury University]] based on the personal papers of Sir [[Erima Harvey Northcroft]], one of the eleven judges on the [[International Military Tribunal for the Far East]]. It is notable because in 2009<ref>{{webarchive |url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20150314125121/http://portal.unesco.org/ci/en/ev.php-URL_ID=29638&URL_DO=DO_TOPIC&URL_SECTION=201.html |title=First inscription from Macao on Memory of the World Register at MOWCAP 4 |date=2015-03-14}}</ref> it was included as one of three [[New Zealand]] entries on the [[UNESCO]] [[Memory of the World Register]].<ref>[http://www.unesco.mowcap.org/register.htm#The%20Tokyo%20War%20Crimes%20Trials%201946-1948 Asia/Pacific Region MOWCAP Register]</ref><ref>[http://www.comsdev.canterbury.ac.nz/news/2010/100427a.shtml UC's war crime archive receives international recognition]</ref>
A comprehensive finding aid has been published.<ref>[http://library.canterbury.ac.nz/mb/war_crimes/toc.shtml Justice Erima Harvey Northcroft Tokyo War Crimes Trial Collection MB1549]</ref> Most of the collection is in the form of bound volumes of news-print quality documents.
