{{Infobox book | name = Tome and Blood | image = Tome and Blood coverthumb.jpg | caption = Cover of ''Tome and Blood'' | author = Bruce R. Cordell, Skip Williams | genre = [[Role-playing game]] | publisher = Wizards of the Coast | release_date = July 2001 | media_type = Print ([[Trade paper edition|Trade Paperback]]) | pages = 96 | isbn = 0-7869-1845-4 | oclc= 47646058 }}
'''''Tome and Blood: A Guidebook to Wizards and Sorcerers''''' is an optional rulebook for the [[Editions of Dungeons & Dragons#Dungeons & Dragons 3rd edition|3rd edition]] of ''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'', and notable for its [[Paperback#Trade paperback|trade paperback]] format.
==Contents== The guidebook provides supplemental information for characters belonging to the [[Wizard (Dungeons & Dragons)|Wizard]] and [[Sorcerer (Dungeons & Dragons)|Sorcerer]] base classes. This book contained tips for creating and playing characters of the aforementioned class, as well as a large number of prestige classes.
''Tome and Blood'' includes 15 prestige classes.{{col-begin}}{{col-3}} *Acolyte of the Skin *Alienist *Arcane Trickster *Bladesinger *Blood Magus {{col-3}} *Candle Caster *Dragon Disciple *Elemental Savant *Fatespinner *Mage of the Arcane Order {{col-3}} *Mindbender *Pale Master *Spellsword *True Necromancer *Wayfarer Guide {{col-end}}
==Publication history== ''Tome and Blood'' was published in 2001 by [[Wizards of the Coast]], and was designed by [[Bruce R. Cordell]] and [[Skip Williams]]. Cover art was by [[Todd Lockwood]], with interior art by [[Wayne Reynolds]].
The book was not updated to 3.5 Edition, although most of the prestige classes were later reintroduced in the 3.5 supplemental sourcebook ''[[Complete Arcane]]''.
==Reception== The reviewer from ''[[Pyramid (magazine)|Pyramid]]'' commented that "In some ways, the theme of ''Tome And Blood'' could be everything old is new again." The reviewer cited the example of the Arcane Order, originally found in the 2nd edition book ''The College of Wizardry'', by [[Bruce R. Cordell]].<ref>http://www.sjgames.com/pyramid/sample.html?id=2309</ref>
